This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with low power wireless communications and proposes a dynamic spectrum access framework for RF-powered ambient backscatter system. It also involves the optimization of system throughput and the reduction of blocking probability and delay, which are important aspects of networking. 

It could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) as it involves the transmission of data over a noisy channel and the optimization of the transmission rate. 

The paper also involves the use of reinforcement learning, which is a popular topic in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

It could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it involves the optimization of a system's performance under dynamic conditions. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of a learning algorithm to optimize the system's performance.
